paper_abstract: H is the theory extending beta-conversion by identifying all closed unsolvables. H omega is the closure of this theory under the omega-rule (and beta-conversion). A long-standing conjecture of H. Barendregt states that the provable equations of H omega form a Pi(1)(1)-complete set. Here we prove that conjecture.
paper_title: SOLUTION OF A PROBLEM OF BARENDREGT ON SENSIBLE lambda-THEORIES
